   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 2635, recto: (1) Phthoumonthes, son of [Paoueris], and his colleagues say (2) to Pamonthes, son of Horus, son of Pa-----: We are paid (3) 4 staters / 2 staters / 4 staters again, for the copper of poll of year 2. (4) Likewise, for the bath (tax) of year 2, 1 kite. (5) [Likewise,] for the dike (tax) of year 1, 1 stater, 1 kite, 4 obols. (6) [Written in year 2 of] Tiberius (7) [Claudius Caesar] Augustus.</ab>
         </div>
